# Copy to env/web.env and point at your backend's reachable address.
# Same shared env/ directory convention as env/server.env — local (non-Docker)
# dev and `vite build`/`vite dev` both read env/web.env via a dotenv.config()
# call at the top of apps/web/vite.config.ts (Vite has no built-in way to point
# its own .env loading at a directory outside the app root).
#
# Must be prefixed VITE_ to be readable from app code (Vite inlines only
# VITE_* vars into the client bundle).
#
# Unlike the server's MONGO_URI, this is the *same* value for local (non-Docker)
# dev and docker compose *when building the web image locally* — it's read by
# the browser, not container-to-container, so it's always "localhost:3000"
# (the server's host-mapped port), never the internal compose service name
# "server":
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
#
# NOT USED at all if docker-compose.yml's web service is running the published
# GHCR image (image: line) instead of building (build: line) — this file is
# never read inside that container. VITE_API_URL was already baked into that
# image whenever it was published (from the VITE_API_URL repo variable at CI
# time, see root README.md's "Releasing" section — defaults to
# http://localhost:3000 if that variable was never set). Only env/server.env
# is read at runtime regardless of build-vs-image mode.
# Only relevant for the Docker image build (docker/web.Dockerfile) — same value,
# passed as a --build-arg instead, since it's inlined at build time, not read
# from this file inside the container (see docker/docker-compose.yml's web
# service and apps/web/README.md's "Production build & Docker" section):
#   docker build --build-arg VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000 ...
#
# INTERNAL_API_URL — NOT read from this file either way. It's a plain runtime
# process.env var (not VITE_-prefixed, so it's never inlined into the client
# bundle) that apps/web/src/lib/api.ts falls back to only when running
# server-side (import.meta.env.SSR), for any call made from inside the web
# container itself rather than the browser — "localhost" inside a container
# means that container, not the separate server container. Set via
# docker-compose.yml's web service `environment:` block instead (already
# wired to "http://server:3000", the compose service name) — nothing to do
# here for docker compose. Not needed at all for plain local (non-Docker)
# `vite dev`/`vite build`, since there's no separate container in that mode.
